node.text:
Full video is now live over on YouTube.com/AlfieDeyes.
.
Over the past 2 weeks I’ve been working on a Vlogumentary (Mix up between a vlog & documentary). Last night the video went live on my YouTube Channel 👌🏻 Here’s a little snippet for you to get the vibe. Please head over and check out the full 35 minute video and be sure to leave a comment letting me know your thoughts. Creating this was very different to anything I’ve uploaded before and I can’t wait to hear what you think. www.YouTube.com/AlfieDeyes

ad • There’s only a bunch of phone cases left from my collaboration with @agoodcom 🙌🏻 (These are purposely limited to reduce any potential wastage).
We’ve also added in a little extra for you! If you use the code ‘ALFIETREE’ on checkout you’ll get 10% off your purchase & @agoodcom will plant 1x extra tree everytime the code is being used, on your behalf via WeForest.
If you’ve already received yours / when you do, please tag me in any posts / stories, I want to see!

node.text:
ad • My phone case collaboration with @AgoodCom is now available 🙌🏻
I’m been an Ambasaador for @AgoodCom for nearly a year now working across a variety of different projects, but by far the most popular / asked about product of theirs that I use every single day is where my phone case is from. So we’ve been behind the scenes working on a creative collaboration for a new phone case! We began the project months ago whilst in strict lockdown which inspired me to design a case which reminds you that Life’s Good every time you see it. I sat down with my designer Lotty (on Zoom), whacked on some good music and both drew up different illustrations / phrases that would bring positivity into people’s lives when they use the case. The phone case itself is climate-positive, made in sweeden and made from organic linseed plants. (It’s also fully biodegradable so you can literally plant it in your garden and it’ll fully biodegrade) The collaborative phone case has just launched over on the @AgoodCom website if you want to purchase one 👌🏼 Oh and be sure to check out their other lovely products too whilst you’re there x
